🔥 3. FIX YOUR HELM DEPLOYMENT (IMPORTANT)

You must pass AWS + kubeconfig into the container

Replace your Helm stage with this:

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

stage('Deploy to EKS (Helm)') {
  steps {
    sh '''
    aws eks update-kubeconfig --region $AWS_REGION --name devops-cluster

    docker run --rm \
      -v $HOME/.kube:/root/.kube \
      -v /home/ec2-user/.aws:/root/.aws \
      -v $(pwd):/workspace \
      -w /workspace \
      alpine/helm:3.14.0 \
      upgrade --install my-app ./helm/my-app \
      --set image.repository=$ECR_REPO \
      --set image.tag=latest
    '''
  }
}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Why this works
.kube → gives cluster access
.aws → gives IAM auth
workspace → gives Helm chart

