THE SOLUTION 

 YOUR CURRENT REALITY

Your Jenkins container is already using:

-v jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home

👉 That means:

All your Jenkins data is stored in a Docker volume ✅
NOT inside the container ❗
🔥 WHAT THIS MEANS
Stopping/removing container ❌ ≠ losing Jenkins data

Your data (jobs, plugins, credentials, webhooks config, etc.) is in:

jenkins_home (Docker volume) ✅
✅ SO YOU ARE SAFE

You can safely:

docker rm jenkins

👉 And NOTHING is lost.

